          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "callout",
              "kind": "bluf",
              "text": "BLUF — A <u>three-driver fundamental case</u> with <u>asymmetric upside</u>, gated by sanctions perimeter and tariff timing; cleanest setup is Demand-Driven EPSU at C-conviction."
            },
            {
              "type": "bullet_group",
              "items": [
                {
                  "iaja": "J",
                  "text": "Three converging __change drivers__ — contracted volume step-up through 2027, regulated price-floor revision pathway, and Yamal terminal de-bottlenecking — combine to a base-case __2-3x re-rate__ over 24-36 months. Structural in nature; not cycle-dependent. Each driver has identifiable quarterly tripwires and observable confirmation events.",
                  "sub": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "A",
                      "text": "Each driver is __independently load-bearing__; combined attribution roughly 65/25/10 to PD#1/PD#2/PD#3 based on preliminary triaging analysis. Cross-ref C.II.2 IC#1 for full pillar detail and RESEARCHER checkpoints."
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "A",
                      "text": "Asymmetric payoff — __downside ~35% to entry__ (capped by P4 bankability floor), upside materially larger (+120% base, +160% with KPOs); suits Demand-Driven EPSU framing on the technical side."
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "A",
                      "text": "Tripwire density — PD#1 reports quarterly via contracted volume update; PD#2 via government regulatory filings; PD#3 via construction milestone releases. __Observable cadence__ supports active monitoring overlay."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "iaja": "J",
                  "text": "Pillars 3 and 4 (Fundamentals + Bankability) carry the fundamental case; Pillar 2 (Paradigm fit) is __supportive but not decisive__; Pillars 1 / 5 / 6 are gating overlays that determine entry timing and position sizing rather than underwriting the case itself.",
                  "sub": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "A",
                      "text": "P3 IC#1 (Three-year ratchet) and IC#2 (Yamal capacity) both rated B; P4 BB#3 (regulated tariff pathway) rated B/C — the three combine to create a structural fundamental case that is __robustly documented__ even at the Triaging stage."
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "A",
                      "text": "P2 (paradigm fit) rated C — energy-security narrative __supports but doesn't drive__ the case; P1 (technical) gates entry via Demand-Driven EPSU confirmation; P5 and P6 provide catalyst visibility and upside quantification."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "iaja": "A",
                  "text": "Setup analysis — __Demand-Driven EPSU__ is the cleaner of the two technical setups present; entry timing requires PD#1 contracted-volume confirmation in the next earnings cycle. Alternative setup (Squeeze-Driven Recovery) is weaker and relies on momentum signals that are less clearly observable for this asset class.",
                  "sub": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "I",
                      "text": "Squeeze-Driven Recovery framing __does not apply cleanly__ — relies on capitulation patterns that are less clearly observable for long-cycle infrastructure assets with regulated revenue components."
                    },
                    {
                      "iaja": "A",
                      "text": "Demand-Driven EPSU confirmation requires: (a) PD#1 contracted volume update in upcoming earnings release; (b) stage-2 base on daily chart; (c) __relative strength__ vs sector peers above 80th percentile."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "iaja": "ACT",
                  "text": "Three downstream actions out of Triaging — progress to ESA; commission RESEARCHER on __tariff comparables__ (Norway / Algeria) for KOQ#4 resolution; schedule IR call to probe tariff revision pathway and contracted volume visibility. Sequencing: commissions in parallel, IR call after both resolve.",
                  "sub": [
                    {
                      "iaja": "ACT",
                      "text": "Also — flag for __monitoring overlay__ regardless of progression decision; sanctions overlay must go live within one week of progression given asymmetric tail risk."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "callout",
              "kind": "summary",
              "text": "Net-net — the case sits in the upper half of the active pipeline by <u>change-driver clarity</u> and the lower half by <u>sanctions overhang</u>. Worth progressing to ESA on the strength of the contracted volume schedule alone. Two open KOQs (Asian re-pricing timeline, tariff cadence) are gating; address both in next stage. Flag for monitoring overlay regardless of progression decision."
